commits.author: Allan Odgaard
commits.summary: Update completion index with functions from the macOS 10.15 SDK
commits.body:
The indexes are now generated via libclang and include a lot more symbols.

Though I did not update CocoaAnnotatedStrings.txt.gz and CocoaAnonymousEnums.txt.gz as I am not entirely sure when these files are used and how, likewise the CocoaNotifications.txt.gz file was updated, but its purpose is not entirely clear to me either.

Once time permits, I will look into the actual completion code and tweak it based on how the macOS SDK has evolved (I assume that the annotated string predates Apple introducing typedefs like NSNotificationName, and changing naming conventions from moving suffix of enumerations into the prefix, so enumeration constants all have the same prefix, rather than having to look at prefix AND suffix).
